[size=4][b]Notes around crafting[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3]If you're not using a multi-inventory/shared inventory mod, the storage for a craft needs to be in the same zone as the crafting station for that station to see the items.[/size]
[*][size=3]If you use a multi-inventory/shared inventory mod, ensure the zone you're building in is included.[/size]
[/list]
[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Build anywhere on the map, not just inside the pre-defined construction zones the game normally limits you to.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Open the Craft Anywhere table[/b] with Q (rebindable) or LB on a controller. It lists every buildable you've unlocked that playthrough — the list is automatically filtered to items that also have a corresponding "remove" craft, so you can always demolish what you place.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Unlock tracking[/b] — items appear in the Craft Anywhere table as you unlock their underlying tech/perk. If a buildable isn't showing up, you haven't researched it yet (or its prerequisite hasn't been learned). The mod respects your progression.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Refugee items hidden[/b] — anything tied to refugee logistics is filtered out because refugees can't use buildings placed outside the refugee camp (it'd be wasted resources).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Hide the yellow construction tape[/b] — optional toggle to suppress the "build-grid" overlay that normally appears inside built-in construction zones. Cleaner view if you're building freehand.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Object collision[/b] stays on by default so you can't overlap a furnace with your front door. You can disable collision at your own risk if you want to stack things freely.[/size]
[*][size=3]Opening the Craft Anywhere table takes a second because the game has a lot of buildables; the first open of a session is the slowest.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — strongly recommended companion. Shared inventory across all zones means you can build anywhere IBWIW lets you, and the station can see materials stored anywhere.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] + [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] + [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] is the classic builder's trio — unlimited placement, queueable crafts, faster build/destroy.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/61]Beam Me Up Gerry[/url] — teleport between zones. Great for distributed builds.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/55]Misc. Bits and Bobs[/url] — movement-speed multiplier if the new build sites are further afield than vanilla expected.[/size]
[/list]

